�������������������������������������������������������������������������������

        Ported Second Reality from mixed C / C++ / Pascal / ASM
        based on (Gargaj / Conspiracy) version to 
        modern, cross-platform C++ targeting 
        Windows (x64/x86), Linux, and WebAssembly


        CREDITS AND ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS
        ----------------------------

        The original code for the demo was done by
          Sami "PSI" Tammilehto
          Mika "Trug" Tuomi
          and Arto "Wildfire" Vuori

        C++ version was done by Jean-Sebastien Royer

        Original Win32 Porting work was done by Gargaj / Conspiracy

        The port uses a heavily modded version of st3play v1.01
        by Olav "8bitbubsy" Sorensen (https://16-bits.org)
        for music replay

        Additional credits and heartfelt thankyous go to
          Trixter / Hornet
            for sharing his considerable knowledge on the workings
            of early EGA/VGA and for some reverse engineering help.
          Saga Musix / Nuance
            for his insight into STMIK and the Scream Tracker
            module format.


        LINKS
        -----

        The original source is available at
          https://github.com/mtuomi/SecondReality

        The Win32 ported source is available at
          https://github.com/ConspiracyHu/SecondRealityW32

        The C++ Windows (x64/x86), Linux, and 
        WebAssembly port source is available at
          https://github.com/XorJS/SecondRealityPlusPlus

        You can get in touch at
          https://www.jsr-productions.com/secondreality.html
          https://x.com/JSRProductions
          https://github.com/XorJS

        Huge thanks to Gargaj/Conspiracy, 
        whose Win32 port inspired this C++ port,
        - JS
